article.headline: Vermont 76, Stony Brook 59
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- T.J. Sorrentine scored 31 points and Taylor Coppenrath added 22 to lead Vermont to its seventh straight victory, 76-59 over Stony Brook on Wednesday night. The Catamounts (10-3, 5-0 America East) are 8-0 all-time against Stony Brook. Jairus McCollum had 14 points for the Seawolves (6-8, 1-4), while Bobby Santiago added 13. Santaigo and McCollum each had four points as Stony Brook took a 14-6 lead. Sorrentine then hit two jumpers to start an 11-0 run for Vermont. Mike Popoko's jumper got the Seawolves even at 27 with 5:07left, but Coppenrath then had eight points as the Catamounts closed the half with a 10-2 run. Sorrentine had nine points in a 23-12 run that gave Vermont a 60-39 lead with 9:54 to go.
